WorkItem.Description:
Hi.

Now TypeScript code

class MyClass {
	public a: number = 0;
}

generate JavaScript code

var MyClass = (function () {
	function MyClass() {
		this.a = 0;
	}
	return MyClass;
})();

Sometimes useful to have private static member.

I.e. TypeScript code

class MyClass {
	public a: number = 0;
	static private b: number = 10;
}

will generate JavaScript code

var MyClass = (function () {
	function MyClass() {
		this.a = 0;
	}
	var b = 10;
	return MyClass;
})();

Thanks
